🏀 Basketball Stats Dashboard

A full-stack application that visualizes basketball stats using a Flask backend and a Next.js frontend. Built to support secure API integration and future OAuth2 authentication.

---

🚀 Project Structure

basketball_stats_dashboard/
├── backend/ # Flask API server
├── frontend/ # Next.js frontend

---

🧰 Tech Stack

- **Backend:** Python, Flask, Flask-CORS
- **Frontend:** Next.js (React), Axios
- **Dev Tools:** Node.js, Git, concurrently, PowerShell
- **Future Features:** OAuth2, API data integration, mobile app via Expo

---

⚙️ Setup Instructions

# Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/basketball_stats_dashboard.git
cd basketball_stats_dashboard

# Backend (Flask)
powershell
Copy code
cd backend
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
python run.py

# Frontend (Next.js)
powershell
cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev

Or run both together:

powershell
npm run dev


🧪 Example API Response
json

GET http://localhost:5000/

{
  "message": "Backend API working!"
}

---

📦 Planned Features
✅ Initial Flask + Next.js setup

